snippet.textDisplay:
Sam, I found your channel during Thanksgiving of 2019. Life's been... interesting. While I had you on as background noise (my husband was hospitalized) I soon began to really listen.

I have 2 teenage sons, 15 and 19, I'm a teacher's assistant in their high school. I say that to say this: you are such a well spoken young man. I see many of the students in a different light than my counterparts - they have hearts such as yours, but they're often dismissed because of their age. I'm Mama Lee to them because I refuse to judge, that's not my job. My "job" is to be there in as much a capacity as I can be.

Your words, (I paraphrase) "I want to bring life and light to others..." is absolutely how I live. Granted it took me a little longer than you, LOL! 😉 My aha moment was the death of my mom 19 years ago when my eldest was 3 months old. It wasn't an overnight transition, more like a decade! 🤦‍♀️

I'm so glad I found your channel. Keep the light shining, you are changing lives for the better, congratulations!

I see many of the students in a different light than my counterparts - they have hearts such as yours, but they're often dismissed because of their age. I'm Mama Lee to them because I refuse to judge, that's not my job. My "job" is to be there in as much a capacity as I can be. 

Your words, (I paraphrase) "I want to bring life and light to others..." is absolutely how I live.  Granted it took me a little longer than you, LOL! 😉 My aha moment was the death of my mom 19 years ago when my eldest was 3 months old. It wasn't an overnight transition, more like a decade! 🤦‍♀️

I'm so glad I found your channel. Keep the light shining, you are changing lives for the better, congratulations!
